body:
I also encountered some error due to dypte conversion.  E.g. `x` is an int32 tensor, then `x = tf.Print(x, [x])` will cause error: `convert from int32 to float32`. 
The other part of my code runs well if I comment this `tf.Print` line.  So I guess there's some hidden operation in `tf.Print()`? But as assumed, `tf.Print()` should do nothing but a `print` operation?
